^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 368 - September 29, 2003^*N
 ^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
This week's deal was played by ^*BKrzysztof Jassem^*N in a tournament to select the Polish team for the upcoming ^*BBermuda Bowl^*N World Champions in Monte Carlo. Jassem was playing with ^*BPiotr Gawrys^*N when this week's deal was played. The deal has been rotated to make South the declarer.

Regular readers of ^*BThe Deal of the Week^*N (not to mention fans of high-level bridge) know that Krzysztof Jassem really stand outs as a great declarer in a country that boasts a remarkable number of world class bridge players.

I would like to thank ^*BMarek Wójcicki^*N for bringing this deal to my attention. Marek is one of the key people behind the ^*BBridge Base Poland^*N web site. One of the main purposes of this web site is to help serve the many Polish members of ^*BBridge Base Online^*N (^*BBBO^*N), but ^*BBridge Base Poland^*N also has an English language area which you can go to in a new browser window by clicking the yellow rectangle below:

|cs|1|at|^-{ ^*Hwww.bridgebase.pl/index2.php^*N }
^-
^*BBBO^*N continues to grow at a remarkable pace. We now have over 1800 people online at peak times each day, over 1000 people online more than half of the time, and over 500 people online even when it is the middle of the night in North America. During the past week people logged in to our site from over 17,000 computers. During the course of any given day there are close to 140,000 logins made to ^*BBBO^*N!
