On October 4th and 5th, the ^*BGerman National Team Qualificiation^*N will be broadcast as ^*Blive^*N vugraph through ^*BBBO^*N. It is also very likely that the ^*B2nd EBL Champions Cup^*N will be broadcast ^*Blive^*N from Rome on October 10th, 11th, and 12th. 8 of Europe's leading bridge countries have been invited to send teams to participate in this event and the bridge rates to be outstanding.

I also am very excited to report that the ^*B2003 World Bridge Championship^*N will be broadcast ^*Blive^*N from Monte Carlo on ^*BBBO^*N from November 2 to 15. This will be the first time that we will feature either the ^*BBermuda Bowl^*N or the ^*BVenice Cup^*N on our site. We are fully expecting to break all kinds of attendence records during this tournament (hopefully our poor server will be able to handle it!).

The details of our broadcasts of the ^*BEBL Champions Cup^*N and the ^*B2003 World Championships^*N have not been completely worked out yet. When we have more information about the exact dates and starting times of these broadcasts the information will be posted at:

